  "body": "Output of `helm version`:\r\n3.1.2\r\n\r\nOutput of `kubectl version`:\r\n1.18.0\r\n\r\nCloud Provider/Platform (AKS, GKE, Minikube etc.): \r\nCentOS Linux release 7.7\r\n\r\nThe same problem still persists in Helm 3.1.2.\r\n[https://github.com/helm/helm/issues/7001](url)\r\n\r\nIf a template contains hook annotation `helm template --output-dir mydir` works incorrectly.\r\nIt does not write generated text for template with a hook to the file.\r\nInstead it prints the output to the console.\r\n\r\n**Example**\r\n```\r\ncat init-job.yaml\r\n\r\napiVersion: batch/v1\r\nkind: Job\r\nmetadata:\r\n  annotations:\r\n    \"helm.sh/hook\": \"post-install\"\r\n    \"helm.sh/hook-weight\": \"0\"\r\n    \"helm.sh/hook-delete-policy\": \"before-hook-creation\"\r\n  name: init\r\n  ...\r\n\r\nhelm template --debug --output-dir /test/out -f values-my.yaml\r\n\r\ninstall.go:158: [debug] Original chart version: \"\"\r\ninstall.go:175: [debug] CHART PATH: /test/mychart\r\n\r\nwrote /test/out/secret.yaml\r\nwrote /test/out/service.yaml\r\n...\r\n\r\n---\r\n# Source: init-job.yaml\r\napiVersion: batch/v1\r\nkind: Job\r\nmetadata:\r\n  annotations:\r\n    \"helm.sh/hook\": \"post-install\"\r\n    \"helm.sh/hook-weight\": \"0\"\r\n    \"helm.sh/hook-delete-policy\": \"before-hook-creation\"\r\n  name: init\r\n  ...\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
